{"title_page": "Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd\n| image               = Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd.jpg\n| image_size          = 200\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1984|2|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Hemsedal]], Norway\n| height              = {{height|m=1.83}}\n| position            = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| currentclub         = [[IL Jardar|Jardar]]\n| clubnumber          = 9\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 = [[Hemsedal IL|Hemsedal]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132007 | clubs1 = [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]]          | caps1 = 42  | goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2006      | clubs2 = \u2192 [[H\u00f8nefoss BK|H\u00f8nefoss]] (loan)  | caps2 = 19  | goals2 = 8\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009 | clubs3 = [[Sandefjord Fotball|Sandefjord]]  | caps3 = 14  | goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2009      | clubs4 = \u2192 [[FK T\u00f8nsberg|T\u00f8nsberg]] (loan)  | caps4 = 26  | goals4 = 23\n| years5 = 2010      | clubs5 = [[Follo Fotball|Follo]]            | caps5 = 27  | goals5 = 13\n| years6 = 2011      | clubs6 = [[Str\u00f8msgodset IF|Str\u00f8msgodset]]   | caps6 = 11  | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[Follo Fotball|Follo]]            | caps7 = 39  | goals7 = 21\n| years8 = 2013      | clubs8 = [[B\u00e6rum SK|B\u00e6rum]]                 | caps8 = 10  | goals8 = 1\n| years9 = 2014\u2013     | clubs9 = [[IL Jardar|Jardar]]               | caps9 = 4   | goals9 = 4\n| nationalyears1      = 2005\n| nationalteam1       = [[Norway national under-21 football team|Norway U-21]]\n| nationalcaps1= 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| club-update         = 16 September 2014\n| nationalteam-update = 26 January 2005\n}}\n'''Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd''' (born 13 February 1984) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for the [[Norwegian fifth Division]] side [[IL Jardar|Jardar]]. He has previously played for [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]] and [[Str\u00f8msgodset IF|Str\u00f8msgodset]] in [[Tippeligaen]] as well as [[H\u00f8nefoss BK|H\u00f8nefoss]], [[Sandefjord Fotball|Sandefjord]], [[FK T\u00f8nsberg|T\u00f8nsberg]] and [[Follo Fotball|Follo]] in lower leagues. Markeg\u00e5rd was runner-up in the [[Norwegian Cup]] in [[2010 Norwegian Football Cup Final|2010]] with Follo.\n\n==Career==\n\nHailing from [[Hemsedal]] in [[Buskerud]], Markeg\u00e5rd was both a talented [[alpine skier]] and [[association football|footballer]],<ref name=\"toppspiss\">{{cite news |url=http://www.nettavisen.no/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/article3026304.ece |language=Norwegian |title=Slik ble han toppspiss igjen |publisher=Nettavisen |first=Marius |last=Vik |date=13 November 2010 |accessdate=22 October 2013}}</ref> but chose to focus on his footballing career in [[Hemsedal IL]] before he moved to [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]] ahead of the [[2002 Tippeligaen|2002 season]]. He made his [[Tippeligaen]] debut in a 4\u20132 win against [[Molde FK|Molde]] on 20 October 2002,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=75382&tournamentId=1&seasonId=333&teamId=328&useFullUrl=false |title=Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd |language=Norwegian |work=altomfotball.no}}</ref> replacing [[Marel Baldvinsson]] in the 86th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=match&matchId=35094&tournamentId=1&seasonId=324&useFullUrl=false |title=Match Report Stab\u00e6k-Molde 20 October 2002 |language=Norwegian |work=altomfotball.no}}</ref> He scored his first goal against [[SK Brann|Brann]], on 20 May 2004, only 3 minutes after he came on a substitute.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=match&matchId=58944&tournamentId=1&seasonId=326&useFullUrl=false |title=Match Report Stab\u00e6k-Brann 20 May 2004 |language=Norwegian |work=altomfotball.no}}</ref> In the [[2006 Norwegian First Division|2006 season]], Markeg\u00e5rd was loaned out to the [[Norwegian First Division|First Division]] club [[H\u00f8nefoss BK|H\u00f8nefoss]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fotball.aftenposten.no/aa/article16100.ece |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120709050454/http://fotball.aftenposten.no/aa/article16100.ece |url-status=dead |archive-date=9 July 2012 |title=Markeg\u00e5rd til H\u00f8nefoss |language=Norwegian |publisher=[[Aftenposten]] |date=3 January 2006 }}</ref> After having scored 8 goals in 19 games, he chose to return to Stab\u00e6k to try to oust Tippeligaen top two strikers, [[Veigar P\u00e1ll Gunnarsson]] and [[Daniel Nannskog]].\n\nMarkeg\u00e5rd scored six goals in his 42 matches for Stab\u00e6k,<ref name=\"toppspiss\" /> and after his contract with the club expired he joined [[Sandefjord Fotball]] on a free transfer ahead of the 2008 season. After playing 14 matches and scoring 2 goals for Sandefjord on the second tier, He was loaned out to third-tier club [[FK T\u00f8nsberg]] in the [[2009 2. Divisjon|2009 season]]. In March 2010 he was released from the contract with Sandefjord and was signed by [[Follo FK|Follo]], where he scored 13 goals in 27 games in the [[2010 Norwegian First Division|2010 season]]. After missing the first round of the [[2010 Norwegian Football Cup|2010 Norwegian Cup]], he scored six goals in the next five rounds,<ref name=\"toppspiss\" /> which made him top goal-scorer in the cup that year,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nifs.no/toppscorer.php?land=1&t=14&u=6034 |title=Toppscorerliste NM Cup 2010 |language=Norwegian |work=nifs.no |publisher=[[A-pressen]]}}</ref> and was a key contributor as Follo came to the [[2009 Norwegian Football Cup|final]], where they lost to [[Str\u00f8msgodset IF|Str\u00f8msgodset]]. After the final, Follo was relegated to the [[Norwegian Second Division|Second Division]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2sporten.no/fotball/adeccoligaen/sandnes-ulf-berget-plassen-i-adeccoligaen-3334295.html |title=Sandnes Ulf berget plassen i Adeccoligaen |publisher=[[TV 2 (Norway)|TV 2]] |date=5 November 2010 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> and Markeg\u00e5rd was released from his contract. He was wanted by [[Sandnes Ulf]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fotball.aftenbladet.no/forstediv/article186968.ece |title=Sandnes Ulf vil ha Markeg\u00e5rd |language=Norwegian |publisher=[[Stavanger Aftenblad]] |date=29 November 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406203634/http://fotball.aftenbladet.no/forstediv/article186968.ece |archivedate=6 April 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> but signed for Str\u00f8msgodset<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dt.no/godset/klare-for-godset-1.6024722 |title=Klare for Godset |language=Norwegian |publisher=[[Drammens Tidende]] |date=11 February 2011}}</ref>\n\nDespite scoring a lot of goals for [[Str\u00f8msgodset IF 2|Str\u00f8msgodset's reserve team]] in the [[Norwegian Second Division|Second Division]], he did not get a lot of chances for the first team in Tippeligaen. In March 2012 he was released by the club, and Markeg\u00e5rd moved back to Follo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oblad.no/sport/markegard-byttet-ut-gullkandidat-i-tippeligaen-med-follo-fk-1.7322200 |language=Norwegian |title=Markeg\u00e5rd byttet ut gullkandidat i Tippeligaen med Follo FK |work=oblad.no |first=Terje |last=Ruud |date=21 May 2012 |accessdate=26 May 2012}}</ref> Markeg\u00e5rd won promotion to the First Division with Follo in 2012, and half-way through the 2013 season he joined the Second Division side [[B\u00e6rum SK|B\u00e6rum]] where he signed a contract till the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.budstikka.no/sport/eirik-markegard-klar-for-berum-1.8006667 |language=Norwegian |title=Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd klar for B\u00e6rum |publisher=Budstikka |first=J\u00f8rgen Dahl |last=Kristiansen |date=7 August 2013 |accessdate=22 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Division\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[2002 Tippeligaen|2002]]\n|rowspan=\"4\" valign=\"center\"|[[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]]\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"|[[Tippeligaen]]\n|1||0||0||0||-||-||1||0\n|-\n|[[2003 Tippeligaen|2003]]\n|1||0||0||0||-||-||1||0\n|-\n|[[2004 Tippeligaen|2004]]\n|11||2||3||0||4||1||18||3\n|-\n|[[2005 Norwegian First Division|2005]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"|[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|25||4||4||2||-||-||29||6\n|-\n|[[2006 Norwegian First Division|2006]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"| [[H\u00f8nefoss BK|H\u00f8nefoss]]\n|19||8||0||0||-||-||19||8\n|-\n|[[2007 Tippeligaen|2007]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Tippeligaen]]\n|4||0||2||1||-||-|||6||1\n|-\n|[[2008 Norwegian First Division|2008]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Sandefjord Fotball|Sandefjord]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|14||2||0||0||-||-||14||2\n|-\n|[[2009 2. Divisjon|2009]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[FK T\u00f8nsberg|T\u00f8nsberg]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[2. Divisjon]]\n|26||23||?||?||-||-||26||23\n|-\n|[[2010 Norwegian First Division|2010]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Follo FK|Follo]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|27||13||6||6||-||-||33||19\n|-\n|[[2011 Tippeligaen|2011]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Str\u00f8msgodset IF|Str\u00f8msgodset]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Tippeligaen]]\n|11||0||3||0||0||0||14||0\n|-\n|[[2012 2. Divisjon|2012]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"|[[Follo Fotball|Follo]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[2. Divisjon]]\n|25||19||1||1||0||0||26||20\n|-\n|[[2013 Norwegian First Division|2013]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|14||2||2||3||0||0||16||5 \n|-\n|[[2013 2. Divisjon|2013]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[B\u00e6rum SK|B\u00e6rum]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[2. Divisjon]]\n|10||1||0||0||0||0||10||1\n|-\n|[[2014 5. Divisjon|2014]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[IL Jardar|Jardar]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|5. Divisjon\n|4||4||0||0||0||0||4||4\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career Total\n!192!!77!!21!!13!!4!!1!!217!!91\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* Top scorer, [[Norwegian Cup]]: 2010\n* Top scorer, [[2. Divisjon]]/1: 2009\n* Top scorer, [[2. Divisjon]]/4: 2012<ref>nifs.no</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Markegard, Eirik}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hemsedal]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Stab\u00e6k Fotball players]]\n[[Category:H\u00f8nefoss BK players]]\n[[Category:Sandefjord Fotball players]]\n[[Category:FK T\u00f8nsberg players]]\n[[Category:Follo FK players]]\n[[Category:Str\u00f8msgodset Toppfotball players]]\n[[Category:B\u00e6rum SK players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:1. divisjon players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd\n| image               = Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd.jpg\n| image_size          = 200\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1984|2|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place         = [[Hemsedal]], Norway\n| height              = {{height|m=1.83}}\n| position            = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| currentclub         = [[IL Jardar|Jardar]]\n| clubnumber          = 9\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 = [[Hemsedal IL|Hemsedal]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132007 | clubs1 = [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]]          | caps1 = 42  | goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2006      | clubs2 = \u2192 [[H\u00f8nefoss BK|H\u00f8nefoss]] (loan)  | caps2 = 19  | goals2 = 8\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009 | clubs3 = [[Sandefjord Fotball|Sandefjord]]  | caps3 = 14  | goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2009      | clubs4 = \u2192 [[FK T\u00f8nsberg|T\u00f8nsberg]] (loan)  | caps4 = 26  | goals4 = 23\n| years5 = 2010      | clubs5 = [[Follo Fotball|Follo]]            | caps5 = 27  | goals5 = 13\n| years6 = 2011      | clubs6 = [[Str\u00f8msgodset IF|Str\u00f8msgodset]]   | caps6 = 11  | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[Follo Fotball|Follo]]            | caps7 = 39  | goals7 = 21\n| years8 = 2013      | clubs8 = [[B\u00e6rum SK|B\u00e6rum]]                 | caps8 = 10  | goals8 = 1\n| years9 = 2014\u2013     | clubs9 = [[IL Jardar|Jardar]]               | caps9 = 4   | goals9 = 4\n| nationalyears1      = 2005\n| nationalteam1       = [[Norway national under-21 football team|Norway U-21]]\n| nationalcaps1= 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n| club-update         = 16 September 2014\n| nationalteam-update = 26 January 2005\n}}\n'''Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd''' (born 13 February 1984) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for the [[Norwegian fifth Division]] side [[IL Jardar|Jardar]]. He has previously played for [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]] and [[Str\u00f8msgodset IF|Str\u00f8msgodset]] in [[Tippeligaen]] as well as [[H\u00f8nefoss BK|H\u00f8nefoss]], [[Sandefjord Fotball|Sandefjord]], [[FK T\u00f8nsberg|T\u00f8nsberg]] and [[Follo Fotball|Follo]] in lower leagues. Markeg\u00e5rd was runner-up in the [[Norwegian Cup]] in [[2010 Norwegian Football Cup Final|2010]] with Follo.\n\n==Career==\n\nHailing from [[Hemsedal]] in [[Buskerud]], Markeg\u00e5rd was both a talented [[alpine skier]] and [[association football|footballer]],<ref name=\"toppspiss\">{{cite news |url=http://www.nettavisen.no/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/article3026304.ece |language=Norwegian |title=Slik ble han toppspiss igjen |publisher=Nettavisen |first=Marius |last=Vik |date=13 November 2010 |accessdate=22 October 2013}}</ref> but chose to focus on his footballing career in [[Hemsedal IL]] before he moved to [[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]] ahead of the [[2002 Tippeligaen|2002 season]]. He made his [[Tippeligaen]] debut in a 4\u20132 win against [[Molde FK|Molde]] on 20 October 2002,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=75382&tournamentId=1&seasonId=333&teamId=328&useFullUrl=false |title=Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd |language=Norwegian |work=altomfotball.no}}</ref> replacing [[Marel Baldvinsson]] in the 86th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=match&matchId=35094&tournamentId=1&seasonId=324&useFullUrl=false |title=Match Report Stab\u00e6k-Molde 20 October 2002 |language=Norwegian |work=altomfotball.no}}</ref> He scored his first goal against [[SK Brann|Brann]], on 20 May 2004, only 3 minutes after he came on a substitute.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=match&matchId=58944&tournamentId=1&seasonId=326&useFullUrl=false |title=Match Report Stab\u00e6k-Brann 20 May 2004 |language=Norwegian |work=altomfotball.no}}</ref> In the [[2006 Norwegian First Division|2006 season]], Markeg\u00e5rd was loaned out to the [[Norwegian First Division|First Division]] club [[H\u00f8nefoss BK|H\u00f8nefoss]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fotball.aftenposten.no/aa/article16100.ece |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120709050454/http://fotball.aftenposten.no/aa/article16100.ece |url-status=dead |archive-date=9 July 2012 |title=Markeg\u00e5rd til H\u00f8nefoss |language=Norwegian |publisher=[[Aftenposten]] |date=3 January 2006 }}</ref> After having scored 8 goals in 19 games, he chose to return to Stab\u00e6k to try to oust Tippeligaen top two strikers, [[Veigar P\u00e1ll Gunnarsson]] and [[Daniel Nannskog]].\n\nMarkeg\u00e5rd scored six goals in his 42 matches for Stab\u00e6k,<ref name=\"toppspiss\" /> and after his contract with the club expired he joined [[Sandefjord Fotball]] on a free transfer ahead of the 2008 season. After playing 14 matches and scoring 2 goals for Sandefjord on the second tier, He was loaned out to third-tier club [[FK T\u00f8nsberg]] in the [[2009 2. Divisjon|2009 season]]. In March 2010 he was released from the contract with Sandefjord and was signed by [[Follo FK|Follo]], where he scored 13 goals in 27 games in the [[2010 Norwegian First Division|2010 season]]. After missing the first round of the [[2010 Norwegian Football Cup|2010 Norwegian Cup]], he scored six goals in the next five rounds,<ref name=\"toppspiss\" /> which made him top goal-scorer in the cup that year,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nifs.no/toppscorer.php?land=1&t=14&u=6034 |title=Toppscorerliste NM Cup 2010 |language=Norwegian |work=nifs.no |publisher=[[A-pressen]]}}</ref> and was a key contributor as Follo came to the [[2009 Norwegian Football Cup|final]], where they lost to [[Str\u00f8msgodset IF|Str\u00f8msgodset]]. After the final, Follo was relegated to the [[Norwegian Second Division|Second Division]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tv2sporten.no/fotball/adeccoligaen/sandnes-ulf-berget-plassen-i-adeccoligaen-3334295.html |title=Sandnes Ulf berget plassen i Adeccoligaen |publisher=[[TV 2 (Norway)|TV 2]] |date=5 November 2010 |language=Norwegian}}</ref> and Markeg\u00e5rd was released from his contract. He was wanted by [[Sandnes Ulf]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fotball.aftenbladet.no/forstediv/article186968.ece |title=Sandnes Ulf vil ha Markeg\u00e5rd |language=Norwegian |publisher=[[Stavanger Aftenblad]] |date=29 November 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406203634/http://fotball.aftenbladet.no/forstediv/article186968.ece |archivedate=6 April 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> but signed for Str\u00f8msgodset<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dt.no/godset/klare-for-godset-1.6024722 |title=Klare for Godset |language=Norwegian |publisher=[[Drammens Tidende]] |date=11 February 2011}}</ref>\n\nDespite scoring a lot of goals for [[Str\u00f8msgodset IF 2|Str\u00f8msgodset's reserve team]] in the [[Norwegian Second Division|Second Division]], he didn't get a lot of chances for the first team in Tippeligaen. In March 2012 he was released by the club, and Markeg\u00e5rd moved back to Follo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oblad.no/sport/markegard-byttet-ut-gullkandidat-i-tippeligaen-med-follo-fk-1.7322200 |language=Norwegian |title=Markeg\u00e5rd byttet ut gullkandidat i Tippeligaen med Follo FK |work=oblad.no |first=Terje |last=Ruud |date=21 May 2012 |accessdate=26 May 2012}}</ref> Markeg\u00e5rd won promotion to the First Division with Follo in 2012, and half-way through the 2013 season he joined the Second Division side [[B\u00e6rum SK|B\u00e6rum]] where he signed a contract till the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.budstikka.no/sport/eirik-markegard-klar-for-berum-1.8006667 |language=Norwegian |title=Eirik Markeg\u00e5rd klar for B\u00e6rum |publisher=Budstikka |first=J\u00f8rgen Dahl |last=Kristiansen |date=7 August 2013 |accessdate=22 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Division\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[2002 Tippeligaen|2002]]\n|rowspan=\"4\" valign=\"center\"|[[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]]\n|rowspan=\"3\" valign=\"center\"|[[Tippeligaen]]\n|1||0||0||0||-||-||1||0\n|-\n|[[2003 Tippeligaen|2003]]\n|1||0||0||0||-||-||1||0\n|-\n|[[2004 Tippeligaen|2004]]\n|11||2||3||0||4||1||18||3\n|-\n|[[2005 Norwegian First Division|2005]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"|[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|25||4||4||2||-||-||29||6\n|-\n|[[2006 Norwegian First Division|2006]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"| [[H\u00f8nefoss BK|H\u00f8nefoss]]\n|19||8||0||0||-||-||19||8\n|-\n|[[2007 Tippeligaen|2007]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Stab\u00e6k Fotball|Stab\u00e6k]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Tippeligaen]]\n|4||0||2||1||-||-|||6||1\n|-\n|[[2008 Norwegian First Division|2008]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Sandefjord Fotball|Sandefjord]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|14||2||0||0||-||-||14||2\n|-\n|[[2009 2. Divisjon|2009]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[FK T\u00f8nsberg|T\u00f8nsberg]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[2. Divisjon]]\n|26||23||?||?||-||-||26||23\n|-\n|[[2010 Norwegian First Division|2010]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Follo FK|Follo]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|27||13||6||6||-||-||33||19\n|-\n|[[2011 Tippeligaen|2011]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Str\u00f8msgodset IF|Str\u00f8msgodset]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Tippeligaen]]\n|11||0||3||0||0||0||14||0\n|-\n|[[2012 2. Divisjon|2012]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"center\"|[[Follo Fotball|Follo]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[2. Divisjon]]\n|25||19||1||1||0||0||26||20\n|-\n|[[2013 Norwegian First Division|2013]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[Adeccoligaen]]\n|14||2||2||3||0||0||16||5 \n|-\n|[[2013 2. Divisjon|2013]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[B\u00e6rum SK|B\u00e6rum]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[2. Divisjon]]\n|10||1||0||0||0||0||10||1\n|-\n|[[2014 5. Divisjon|2014]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|[[IL Jardar|Jardar]]\n|rowspan=\"1\" valign=\"center\"|5. Divisjon\n|4||4||0||0||0||0||4||4\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career Total\n!192!!77!!21!!13!!4!!1!!217!!91\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* Top scorer, [[Norwegian Cup]]: 2010\n* Top scorer, [[2. Divisjon]]/1: 2009\n* Top scorer, [[2. Divisjon]]/4: 2012<ref>nifs.no</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Markegard, Eirik}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hemsedal]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Stab\u00e6k Fotball players]]\n[[Category:H\u00f8nefoss BK players]]\n[[Category:Sandefjord Fotball players]]\n[[Category:FK T\u00f8nsberg players]]\n[[Category:Follo FK players]]\n[[Category:Str\u00f8msgodset Toppfotball players]]\n[[Category:B\u00e6rum SK players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:1. divisjon players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n", "name_user": "Sct72", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCareer", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eirik_Markeg%C3%A5rd"}
{"title_page": "Mark Gurashi", "text_new": "{{short description|Albanian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Mark Gurashi\n| image =\n| fullname = Mark Gurashi\n| birth_date = \n| death_date = \n| height = \n| currentclub = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 =    \n| youthclubs1 =   \n| years1 = 1930\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[SK Tirana|Tirana]]\n| caps1 =\n| goals1 =\n| nationalyears1 =   \n| nationalteam1 =   \n| nationalcaps1 =     \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate = \n}}\n\n'''Mark Gurashi''' was [[Albania]]n football player who played for [[SK Tirana]] during the 1930s, where he won the [[Kategoria superiore]] five times in just seven years and where he also won the golden boot for the 1934 season after scoring 12 league goals,<ref>[http://telegraf.al/sport/kepucet-e-arta-te-shqiperise-nga-refik-resmja-te-iir-pernaska/ \u201cK\u00ebpuc\u00ebt e Arta\u201d t\u00eb Shqip\u00ebris\u00eb, nga Refik Resmja te Iir P\u00ebrnaska] - Telegraf {{in lang|sq}}</ref> which was the highest tally in a season since the league was created in 1930.<ref>[http://www.giovanniarmillotta.it/albania/calcio/alba34.html Albanian Football Season 1934]</ref><ref>[http://www.giovanniarmillotta.it/albania/calcio/championship.html Albanian National Championships]</ref>\n\n== SK Tirana ==\nHe featured in the 1st ever Albanian football championship, the [[Kategoria superiore 1930]], a competition which he also won for the very first time in 1930. With SK Tirana he managed to win 5 championship titles, including the first ever one in 1930.\n\n==Honours==\n*'''[[Albanian Superliga]]: 5''' \n:: [[1930 Albanian Superliga|1930]], [[1931 Albanian Superliga|1931]], [[1932 Albanian Superliga|1932]], [[1936 Albanian Superliga|1936]], [[1937 Albanian Superliga|1937]] <ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/players/alba-champ-teams.html Albania - Championship Winning Teams] - RSSSF</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Albanian Superliga top scorers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gurashi, Mark}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Albanian footballers]]\n[[Category:KF Tirana players]]\n[[Category:Albanian Superliga players]]\n\n\n\n\n{{Albania-footy-forward-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Mark Gurashi\n| image =\n| fullname = Mark Gurashi\n| birth_date = \n| death_date = \n| height = \n| currentclub = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 =    \n| youthclubs1 =   \n| years1 = 1930\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[SK Tirana|Tirana]]\n| caps1 =\n| goals1 =\n| nationalyears1 =   \n| nationalteam1 =   \n| nationalcaps1 =     \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = \n| ntupdate = \n}}\n\n'''Mark Gurashi''' was [[Albania]]n football player who played for [[SK Tirana]] during the 1930s, where he won the [[Kategoria superiore]] five times in just seven years and where he also won the golden boot for the 1934 season after scoring 12 league goals,<ref>[http://telegraf.al/sport/kepucet-e-arta-te-shqiperise-nga-refik-resmja-te-iir-pernaska/ \u201cK\u00ebpuc\u00ebt e Arta\u201d t\u00eb Shqip\u00ebris\u00eb, nga Refik Resmja te Iir P\u00ebrnaska] - Telegraf {{in lang|sq}}</ref> which was the highest tally in a season since the league was created in 1930.<ref>[http://www.giovanniarmillotta.it/albania/calcio/alba34.html Albanian Football Season 1934]</ref><ref>[http://www.giovanniarmillotta.it/albania/calcio/championship.html Albanian National Championships]</ref>\n\n== SK Tirana ==\nHe featured in the 1st ever Albanian football championship, the [[Kategoria superiore 1930]], a competition which he also won for the very first time in 1930. With SK Tirana he managed to win 5 championship titles, including the first ever one in 1930.\n\n==Honours==\n*'''[[Albanian Superliga]]: 5''' \n:: [[1930 Albanian Superliga|1930]], [[1931 Albanian Superliga|1931]], [[1932 Albanian Superliga|1932]], [[1936 Albanian Superliga|1936]], [[1937 Albanian Superliga|1937]] <ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/players/alba-champ-teams.html Albania - Championship Winning Teams] - RSSSF</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Albanian Superliga top scorers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gurashi, Mark}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Albanian footballers]]\n[[Category:KF Tirana players]]\n[[Category:Albanian Superliga players]]\n\n\n\n\n{{Albania-footy-forward-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"Albanian footballer\", overriding Wikidata description \"Albanian footballer\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Gurashi"}
{"title_page": "Safet Osja", "text_new": "{{short description|Albanian footballer}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2010}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Safet Osja\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1975|10|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Shkod\u00ebr]], [[Albania]]\n| height = {{convert|1.93|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| years1 = 1995\u20131997 \n| years2 = 1997\u20132004 \n| years3 = 2004\u20132006 \n| years4 = 2006\u20132010 \n| years5 = 2010\u20132012 \n| clubs1 = [[KF La\u00e7i|La\u00e7i]] \n| clubs2 = [[KS Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia]] \n| clubs3 = [[KS Elbasani|Elbasani]] \n| clubs4 = [[KS Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia]] \n| clubs5 = [[KS Ada Velipoj\u00eb|Ada]]\n| caps1 = 41  \n| caps2 = 164  \n| caps3 = 70  \n| caps4 = 112   \n| caps5 = 10  \n| goals1 = 0  \n| goals2 = 3  \n| goals3 = 1  \n| goals4 = 4  \n| goals5 = 5 \n| totalcaps = 397 | totalgoals = 13\n| nationalyears1 =  \n| nationalteam1 =   [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albania U-21]]\n| nationalcaps1 =    1  \n| nationalgoals1 =   0 \n}}\n\n'''Safet Osja''' (born 17 October 1975) is an [[Albania]]n retired [[association football|footballer]] who last played as a [[midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] <ref name=uefa>[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/clubs/player=34452/index.html UEFA stats]</ref> for [[KS Ada Velipoj\u00eb]] in the [[Albanian First Division]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/players/safet-osja/41112/ Player stats at soccerway]</ref> \n\nOsja was previously with [[KS Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr]] and he played for them in the [[2009\u201310 UEFA Europa League]].<ref name=uefa/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://fshf.org/garat/?query=info&player_id=214600 Profile] \u2013 FSHF\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Osja, Safet}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Shkod\u00ebr]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Albanian footballers]]\n[[Category:Albania under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:KF La\u00e7i players]]\n[[Category:KF Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr players]]\n[[Category:KF Elbasani players]]\n[[Category:KS Ada Velipoj\u00eb players]]\n[[Category:Albanian Superliga players]]\n[[Category:Albanian First Division players]]\n\n\n{{Albania-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=March 2010}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Safet Osja\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1975|10|17}}\n| birth_place = [[Shkod\u00ebr]], [[Albania]]\n| height = {{convert|1.93|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| years1 = 1995\u20131997 \n| years2 = 1997\u20132004 \n| years3 = 2004\u20132006 \n| years4 = 2006\u20132010 \n| years5 = 2010\u20132012 \n| clubs1 = [[KF La\u00e7i|La\u00e7i]] \n| clubs2 = [[KS Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia]] \n| clubs3 = [[KS Elbasani|Elbasani]] \n| clubs4 = [[KS Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia]] \n| clubs5 = [[KS Ada Velipoj\u00eb|Ada]]\n| caps1 = 41  \n| caps2 = 164  \n| caps3 = 70  \n| caps4 = 112   \n| caps5 = 10  \n| goals1 = 0  \n| goals2 = 3  \n| goals3 = 1  \n| goals4 = 4  \n| goals5 = 5 \n| totalcaps = 397 | totalgoals = 13\n| nationalyears1 =  \n| nationalteam1 =   [[Albania national under-21 football team|Albania U-21]]\n| nationalcaps1 =    1  \n| nationalgoals1 =   0 \n}}\n\n'''Safet Osja''' (born 17 October 1975) is an [[Albania]]n retired [[association football|footballer]] who last played as a [[midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] <ref name=uefa>[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/clubs/player=34452/index.html UEFA stats]</ref> for [[KS Ada Velipoj\u00eb]] in the [[Albanian First Division]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/players/safet-osja/41112/ Player stats at soccerway]</ref> \n\nOsja was previously with [[KS Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr]] and he played for them in the [[2009\u201310 UEFA Europa League]].<ref name=uefa/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External lin