{"title_page": "Emil Hajnali", "text_new": "{{short description|Albanian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Emil Hajnali\n| image =\n| fullname = Emil Hajnali\n| birth_date = \n| death_date = \n| height = \n| currentclub = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 =    \n| youthclubs1 =   \n| years1 =   1930\u2013????\n| clubs1 =   [[SK Tirana]]\n| caps1 =     ? \n| goals1 =  ? \n| nationalyears1 =   \n| nationalteam1 =   \n| nationalcaps1 =     \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = 18 January 2010\n| ntupdate = 18 January 2010\n}}\n'''Emil Hajnali''' was a former [[Albania]]n football player who played for [[SK Tirana]] during the 1930s, where he won the [[Kategoria superiore]] five times in just seven years and where he also won the first ever golden boot in Albanian history after scoring 3 goals in the 1930 championship.\n\n== SK Tirana ==\nHe featured in the 1st ever Albanian football championship, the [[Kategoria superiore 1930]], a competition which he also won for the very first time in 1930.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/85-vjet-me-pare-kampionati-i-1-re-i-shqiperise/ 85 vjet m\u00eb par\u00eb: Kampionati i 1-r\u00eb i Shqip\u00ebris\u00eb] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref> He was the joint top scorer of the competition in 1930 alongside teammate [[Rexhep Ma\u00e7i]] with 3 goals in a possible 10 games.<ref>[http://telegraf.al/sport/kepucet-e-arta-te-shqiperise-nga-refik-resmja-te-iir-pernaska/ \u201cK\u00ebpuc\u00ebt e Arta\u201d t\u00eb Shqip\u00ebris\u00eb, nga Refik Resmja te Iir P\u00ebrnaska] - Telegraf {{in lang|sq}}</ref> With SK Tirana he managed to win 5 championship titles, including the first ever one in 1930. He won the Kategoria superiore in 1930, 1931, 1932, 1936 and 1937.<ref>[https://google.com/search?q=cache:e3QO3VoN6S8J:www.rsssf.com/players/alba-champ-teams.html+%22Emil+Hajnali%22&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk Championship Winning Teams]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{use dmy dates|date=December 2010}}\n{{Albanian Superliga top scorers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hajnali, Emil}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Possibly living people]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Albanian footballers]]\n[[Category:KF Tirana players]]\n\n\n{{Albania-footy-forward-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Emil Hajnali\n| image =\n| fullname = Emil Hajnali\n| birth_date = \n| death_date = \n| height = \n| currentclub = \n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 =    \n| youthclubs1 =   \n| years1 =   1930\u2013????\n| clubs1 =   [[SK Tirana]]\n| caps1 =     ? \n| goals1 =  ? \n| nationalyears1 =   \n| nationalteam1 =   \n| nationalcaps1 =     \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = 18 January 2010\n| ntupdate = 18 January 2010\n}}\n'''Emil Hajnali''' was a former [[Albania]]n football player who played for [[SK Tirana]] during the 1930s, where he won the [[Kategoria superiore]] five times in just seven years and where he also won the first ever golden boot in Albanian history after scoring 3 goals in the 1930 championship.\n\n== SK Tirana ==\nHe featured in the 1st ever Albanian football championship, the [[Kategoria superiore 1930]], a competition which he also won for the very first time in 1930.<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/85-vjet-me-pare-kampionati-i-1-re-i-shqiperise/ 85 vjet m\u00eb par\u00eb: Kampionati i 1-r\u00eb i Shqip\u00ebris\u00eb] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref> He was the joint top scorer of the competition in 1930 alongside teammate [[Rexhep Ma\u00e7i]] with 3 goals in a possible 10 games.<ref>[http://telegraf.al/sport/kepucet-e-arta-te-shqiperise-nga-refik-resmja-te-iir-pernaska/ \u201cK\u00ebpuc\u00ebt e Arta\u201d t\u00eb Shqip\u00ebris\u00eb, nga Refik Resmja te Iir P\u00ebrnaska] - Telegraf {{in lang|sq}}</ref> With SK Tirana he managed to win 5 championship titles, including the first ever one in 1930. He won the Kategoria superiore in 1930, 1931, 1932, 1936 and 1937.<ref>[https://google.com/search?q=cache:e3QO3VoN6S8J:www.rsssf.com/players/alba-champ-teams.html+%22Emil+Hajnali%22&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk Championship Winning Teams]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{use dmy dates|date=December 2010}}\n{{Albanian Superliga top scorers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hajnali, Emil}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Possibly living people]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Albanian footballers]]\n[[Category:KF Tirana players]]\n\n\n{{Albania-footy-forward-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"Albanian footballer\", overriding Wikidata description \"Albanian footballer\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emil_Hajnali"}
{"title_page": "Roberto Brunamonti", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian basketball player}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name            = Roberto Brunamonti\n| image           = Roberto Brunamonti.jpg\n| image_size      = 250px\n| caption         = Brunamonti with [[Virtus Pallacanestro Bologna|Virtus]], in the 1980s.\n| position        = \n| height_ft       = 6\n| height_in       = 3\n| weight_lbs      = 180\n| league          = \n| team            = \n| number          = \n| nationality     = Italian\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1959|4|14}}\n| birth_place     = [[Spoleto]], [[Italy]]\n| college         =\n| high_school     =\n| draft_round     = \n| draft_pick      = \n| draft_year      = \n| draft_team      = \n| career_start    = 1975\n| career_end      = 1996\n| career_number   =\n| career_position = [[Point guard]]\n| years1          = 1975\u20131982\n| team1           = [[AMG Sebastiani Basket]]\n| years2          = 1982\u20131996\t\n| team2           = [[Virtus Pallacanestro Bologna|Virtus Bologna]]\n| years3          = \n| team3           = \n| years4          =\n| team4           = \n| years5          = \n| team5           = \n| years6          = \n| team6           = \n| years7          = \n| team7           =\n| years8          = \n| team8           = \n| years9          = \n| team9           = \n| highlights      = \n'''As a player''':\n*[[FIBA European Selection]] (1991)\n*[[FIBA Saporta Cup]] champion (1990)\n*[[FIBA Kora\u0107 Cup]] champion (1980)\n*4\u00d7 [[Lega Basket Serie A|Italian League]] champion (1984, 1993, 1994, 1995)\n*3\u00d7 [[Italian Basketball Cup|Italian Cup]] winner (1984, 1989, 1990)\n*[[Italian Basketball Supercup|Italian Supercup]] winner (1995)\n'''As a head coach:'''\n*[[Italian Basketball Cup|Italian Cup]] winner (1997)\n| medaltemplates  =\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[Basketball]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{bk|ITA}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Basketball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver | [[Basketball at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Moscow]] | }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[EuroBasket]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[EuroBasket 1983|1983 France]] | }}\n{{MedalBronze | [[EuroBasket 1985|1985 West Germany]] | }}\n{{MedalSilver| [[EuroBasket 1991|1991 Italy]] | }}\n}}\n\n'''Roberto Brunamonti''' (born April 14, 1959 in [[Spoleto]]) is a retired [[Italy|Italian]] professional [[basketball]] player and [[basketball coach|coach]]. At a height of 191&nbsp;cm (6'3\") tall, he played at the [[point guard]] position. He was among the 105 player nominees for the [[50 Greatest EuroLeague Contributors]] list.\n\n==Professional career==\nBrunamonti started his career with [[AMG Sebastiani Basket Rieti]], in 1975, and after seven years, joined [[Virtus Pallacanestro Bologna|Virtus Bologna]] in 1982. He played with Virtus Bologna, until he ended his career in 1996, after playing 21 years in the [[Lega Basket Serie A|Italian basketball league]].\n\nHe won four [[Lega Basket Serie A|Italian League]] championships (1984, 1993, 1994, 1995), three [[Italian Basketball Cup|Italian Cups]] (1984, 1989, 1990), and one [[Italian Basketball Supercup|Italian Supercup]] (1995).\n\n==National team career==\nBrunamonti won the silver medal with the senior [[Italian national basketball team]], at the [[Basketball at the 1980 Summer Olympics|1980 Summer Olympic Games]] in [[Moscow]].\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://archive.fiba.com/pages/eng/fa/p/rpp//q/Roberto%20Brunamonti/pid//_//players.html FIBA Profile]\n*[http://www.fibaeurope.com/compID_,Uz02qBnJiADOq5VntEf53.season_1993.roundID_2564.teamID_1315.playerID_7670.html FIBA Europe Profile]\n*[http://web.legabasket.it/player/?id=BRU-ROB-59 Italian League Profile] {{in lang|it}}\n*{{IOC profile|roberto-brunamonti}}\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Italy Men Basketball Squad 1980 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Italy Squad EuroBasket 1991}}\n}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brunamonti, Roberto}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:AMG Sebastiani Basket players]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Basketball players at the 1984 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:FIBA EuroBasket-winning players]]\n[[Category:Italian basketball coaches]]\n[[Category:Italian men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1980 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic basketball players of Italy]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in basketball]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for Italy]]\n[[Category:People from Spoleto]]\n[[Category:Point guards]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Umbria]]\n[[Category:Virtus Pallacanestro Bologna players]]\n[[Category:1986 FIBA World Championship players]]\n\n\n{{Italy-basketball-bio-stub}}\n{{Italy-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian basketball player}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name            = Roberto Brunamonti\n| image           = Roberto Brunamonti.jpg\n| image_size      = 250px\n| caption         = Brunamonti with [[Virtus Pallacanestro Bologna|Virtus]], in the 1980s.\n| position        = \n| height_ft       = 6\n| height_in       = 3\n| weight_lbs      = 180\n| league          = \n| team            = \n| number          = \n| nationality     = Italian\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1959|4|14}}\n| birth_place     = [[Spoleto]], [[Italy]]\n| college         =\n| high_school     =\n| draft_round     = \n| draft_pick      = \n| draft_year      = \n| draft_team      = \n| career_start    = 1975\n| career_end      = 1996\n| career_number   =\n| career_position = [[Point guard]]\n| years1          = 1975\u20131982\n| team1           = [[AMG Sebastiani Basket]]\n| years2          = 1982\u20131996\t\n| team2           = [[Virtus Pallacanestro Bologna|Virtus Bologna]]\n| years3          = \n| team3           = \n| years4          =\n| team4           = \n| years5          = \n| team5           = \n| years6          = \n| team6           = \n| years7          = \n| team7           =\n| years8